<subSubSection pageId="278" pageNumber="883" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="278.[1400,2606,3040,3478]" pageId="278" pageNumber="883">
On the basis of morphological differences, G. B. Corbet and J. E. Hill in1992 suggested that 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Yang &amp; Wang" authorityYear="1987" box="[1562,1764,3327,3361]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Hadromys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="278" pageNumber="883" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="yunnanensis">H. yunnanensis</taxonomicName>
was a valid species,an opinion followed by G. G.Musser and M. D. Carleton in 2005. Monotypic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
