<subSubSection lastPageId="279" lastPageNumber="884" pageId="278" pageNumber="883" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="278.[1400,2606,3040,3478]" lastBlockId="279.[779,1371,290,718]" lastPageId="279" lastPageNumber="884" pageId="278" pageNumber="883">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1401,1652,3449,3478]" pageId="278" pageNumber="883">Descriptive notes.</emphasis>
Head-body 123-136 mm, tail 114-132 mm, ear 14-15 mm, hindfoot 22-24 mm; weight 41-77 g. The Yunnan 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thomas" authorityYear="1911" box="[842,986,335,369]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Hadromys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="279" pageNumber="884" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Hadromys</taxonomicName>
is a small murid, characterized by having bicolored tail shorter than head-body length, soft and dense fur, and slender hindfeet. Dorsum is dark gray brown, sprinkled with black, yellow, or white hair; venter is pure white. Females have four pairs of mammae.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="279" pageNumber="884" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="279.[779,1371,290,718]" pageId="279" pageNumber="884">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[779,890,606,640]" pageId="279" pageNumber="884">Habitat.</emphasis>
Found at elevations of 970-1300 m; no further details about habitat preferences are available.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
